[18.089644, "o", "\u001b[22S\u001b[H\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[2m[ 5] \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[94m\u001b[1mhuggingface-gradio\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n     Build Gradio web UIs and demos in Python. Use when creating or editing\u001b[K\r\n     Gradio apps, components, event listeners, layouts, or chatbots.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[2m     \u001b[32msource: skill://huggingface-gradio/SKILL.md\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[2m[ 6] \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[94m\u001b[1mhuggingface-llm-trainer\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n     Train or fine-tune language and vision models using TRL (Transformer\u001b[K\r\n     Reinforcement Learning) or Unsloth with Hugging Face Jobs\u001b[K\r\n     infrastructure. Covers SFT, DPO, GRPO and reward modeling training\u001b[K\r\n     methods, plus GGUF conversion for local deployment. Includes guidance on\u001b[K\r\n     the TRL Jobs package, UV scripts with PEP 723 format, dataset\u001b[K\r\n     preparation and validation, hardware selection, cost estimation, Trackio\u001b[K\r\n     monitoring, Hub authentication, model selection/leaderboards and model\u001b[K\r\n     persistence. Use for tasks involving cloud GPU training, GGUF\u001b[K\r\n     conversion, or when users mention training on Hugging Face Jobs without\u001b[K\r\n     local GPU setup.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[2m     \u001b[32msource: skill://huggingface-llm-trainer/SKILL.md\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[2m[ 7] \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[94m\u001b[1mhuggingface-local-models\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n     Use to select models to run locally with llama.cpp and GGUF on CPU, Mac\u001b[K\r\n     Metal, CUDA, or ROCm. Covers finding GGUFs, quant \u001b[K\r\u001b[22S\u001b[H     summarize, explain, or analyze an AI research paper.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[2m     \u001b[32msource: skill://huggingface-papers/SKILL.md\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[2m[10] \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[94m\u001b[1mhuggingface-tool-builder\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n     Use this skill when the user wants to build tool/scripts or achieve a\u001b[K\r\n     task where using data from the Hugging Face API would help. This is\u001b[K\r\n     especially useful when chaining or combining API calls or the task will\u001b[K\r\n     be repeated/automated. This Skill creates a reusable script to fetch,\u001b[K\r\n     enrich or process data.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[2m     \u001b[32msource: skill://huggingface-tool-builder/SKILL.md\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[2m[11] \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[94m\u001b[1mhuggingface-trackio\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n     Track and visualize ML training experiments with Trackio. Use when\u001b[K\r\n     logging metrics during training (Python API), firing alerts for training\u001b[K\r\n     diagnostics, or retrieving/analyzing logged metrics (CLI). Supports\u001b[K\r\n     real-time dashboard visualization, alerts with webhooks, HF Space\u001b[K\r\n     syncing, and JSON output for automation.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[2m     \u001b[32msource: skill://huggingface-trackio/SKILL.md\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[2m[12] \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[94m\u001b[1mhuggingface-vision-trainer\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n     Trains and fine-tunes vision models for object detection (D-FINE, RT-\u001b[K\r\n     DETR v2, DETR, YOLOS), image classification (timm models \u001b[K—\r\n\u001b[21;64H MobileNetV3,\r\n     MobileViT, ResNet, ViT/DINOv3 \u001b[K—\r\u001b[16S\u001b[6;37H plus any Transformers classifier), and\r\n     SAM/SAM2 segmentation using Hugging Face Transformers on Hugging Face\u001b[K\r\n     Jobs cloud GPUs. Covers COCO-format dataset preparation, Albumentations\u001b[K\r\n     augmentation, mAP/mAR evaluation, accuracy metrics, SAM segmentation\u001b[K\r\n     with bbox/point prompts, DiceCE loss, hardware selection, cost\u001b[K\r\n     estimation, Trackio monitoring, and Hub persistence. Use when users\u001b[K\r\n     mention training object detection, image classification, SAM, SAM2,\u001b[K\r\n     segmentation, image matting, DETR, D-FINE, RT-DETR, ViT, timm,\u001b[K\r\n     MobileNet, ResNet, bounding box models, or fine-tuning vision models on\u001b[K\r\n     Hugging Face Jobs.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[2m     \u001b[32msource: skill://huggingface-vision-trainer/SKILL.md\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[2m[13] \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[94m\u001b[1mhuggingface-zerogpu\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n     AI demos and GPU compute with Gradio Spaces and Hugging Face Spaces\u001b[K\r\n     ZeroGPU. Use when writing or reviewing code that uses `@spaces.GPU`,\u001b[K\r\n     configuring `python_version` or `requirements.txt` for a ZeroGPU Space,\u001b[K\r\n     or handling ZeroGPU-specific code constraints \u001b[K—\r\u001b[7S\u001b[15;53H pickle-based process\r\n     isolation, `gr.State` semantics across the worker boundary, no\u001b[K\r\n     `torch.compile` (use AoTI instead), CUDA wheel-only builds (no `nvcc` at\u001b[K\r\n     build or runtime), large vs xlarge sizing, and dynamic duration\u001b[K\r\n     callables. Make sure to use this skill whenever the user mentions\u001b[K\r\n     ZeroGPU, `@spaces.GPU`, or the `spaces` Python package, or hits ZeroGPU-\u001b[K\r\n     specific code errors like `PicklingError` across the worker boundary,\u001b[K\r\n     `illegal duration`, or `flash-attn` wheel-build failures \u001b[K—\r\u001b[6S\u001b[16;64H even when the\r\n     user does not explicitly ask for ZeroGPU coding guidance. Trigger on\u001b[K\r\n     `import spaces` or `@spaces.GPU` in code.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[2m     \u001b[32msource: skill://huggingface-zerogpu/SKILL.md\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[2m[14] \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[94m\u001b[1mtrain-sentence-transformers\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n     Train or fine-tune se\u001b[K\r\u001b[22S\u001b[H     `SentenceTransformer` (bi-encoder; dense or static embedding model; for\u001b[K\r\n     retrieval, similarity, clustering, classification, paraphrase mining,\u001b[K\r\n     dedup, multimodal), `CrossEncoder` (reranker; pair scoring for two-stage\u001b[K\r\n     retrieval / pair classification), and `SparseEncoder` (SPLADE, sparse\u001b[K\r\n     embedding model; for learned-sparse retrieval). Covers loss selection,\u001b[K\r\n     hard-negative mining, evaluators, distillation, LoRA, Matryoshka, and\u001b[K\r\n     Hugging Face Hub publishing. Use for any sentence-transformers training\u001b[K\r\n     task.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[2m     \u001b[32msource: skill://train-sentence-transformers/SKILL.md\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[2m[15] \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[94m\u001b[1mtransformers-js\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n     Use Transformers.js to run state-of-the-art machine learning models\u001b[K\r\n     directly in JavaScript/TypeScript. Supports NLP (text classification,\u001b[K\r\n     translation, summarization), computer vision (image classification,\u001b[K\r\n     object detection), audio (speech recognition, audio classification), and\u001b[K\r\n     multimodal tasks. Works in browsers and server-side runtimes (Node.js,\u001b[K\r\n     Bun, Deno) with WebGPU/WASM using pre-trained models from Hugging Face\u001b[K\r\n     Hub.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[2m     \u001b[32msource: skill://transformers-js/SKILL.md\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K"]
